President Obama has nominated Terrence G. Berg, Jesus G. Bernal, Shelly Deckert Dick, and Lorna G. Schofield to serve on the United States District Court. Terrence G. Berg has been an Assistant United States Attorney since 1989 and has served in various roles within the Department of Justice. Jesus G. Bernal has been a Deputy Federal Public Defender since 1996. Shelly Deckert Dick is a partner at a law firm in Baton Rouge and has been a litigator for 24 years. Lorna G. Schofield has been affiliated with a law firm in New York City since 1988 and has experience in complex civil litigation and white collar criminal defense.